newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline up $10 with NYMEX, local demand.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline up $10 with NYMEX, local demand.

text.p: NWE gasoline jumped $10 per tonne after two days of strong gains in New York and widespread buying interest in Europe, traders said.
Premium unleaded barges traded up to $231.00 per tonne fob ARA, having begun the day at $224.00, and cargo bids rose to $235 cif Thames, with offers all the way up at $240 cif.

Cargo buying was reported in Poland, Germany and the U.K., the latter particularly ahead of the end-November budget when excise duty is expected to rise sharply. Some U.S. traders were looking for low octane material for a back-haul voyage on vessels used to bring low sulphur gas oil to Europe.
